              the Guide is immeasurably enhanced by the replacement of the old
              street planswith new, clear versions of the itineraries that
              structure a volume which remains the unrivalled guide to perhaps
              the most beautiful and historic city in the world. John Fort, who
              has lived in the city for the past thirty years, walked every step
              of the routes described so vividly by Georgina Masson, and many
              more besides. In addition to checking and updating the information
              she provided so inimitably, he uncovered and describes a wealth of
              sights which slipped her notice, and accompanies the visitor
              through all the major museums and galleries as now arranged. The
              result is a guide to that incomparable array of classical,
